## The Living Directory of Business Ideas

Welcome to your business idea hub. Instead of a long list, we've organized 50+ proven business models by type so you can find what matches your skills and timeline.

**Most people spend 3-6 months building a business idea that nobody wants to buy.** The smart move? [Validate your idea first](/start/niche-selection), then pick a model that matches your starting point.

Not sure which direction to go? Start by asking:
- **Do I need immediate cash?** → Digital Services (revenue in 30-90 days)
- **Do I have an audience?** → Digital Products (scale with automation)
- **Do I want to build a tool?** → SaaS/Tools (highest revenue potential but longest timeline)
- **Am I location-based?** → Local Services (high demand, personal touch)

---

## Digital Services

Fast cash flow, zero startup cost, revenue in 30-60 days.

These work because you solve someone's problem immediately and they pay you right away.

The internet has flipped the economics of business upside-down. What required a team of 5-10 people in 2005 one person can now do alone. Automation tools, AI, and no-code platforms let solo founders handle work that previously required multiple employees.

A one-person business lets you keep 75-90% of revenue, scale without scaling hours, charge 2-3x more for expertise, and maintain complete control.

---

## Browse By Type

### Digital Services — 6 options

**Revenue timeline:** 30-90 days | **Startup cost:** $0-100/month

Service-based income is the fastest path to revenue. You sell your time and expertise solving specific problems.

- **[Copywriting](/start/business-ideas/digital-services/copywriting)** — $3K-10K+ per project. Write sales pages, email sequences, landing pages for SaaS and coaches.
- **[Video Editing](/start/business-ideas/digital-services/video-editing)** — $500-5K/month. Edit YouTube videos, Reels, podcasts for creators and agencies.
- **[Social Media Management](/start/business-ideas/digital-services/social-media-management)** — $1.5K-5K per client. Manage 6-8 accounts systematically. Batch content to scale.
- **[Virtual Assistant](/start/business-ideas/digital-services/virtual-assistant)** — $2K-4K/month. Admin, scheduling, email, operations for entrepreneurs.
- **[Bookkeeping/Tax Specialist](#)** — $2K-5K/month retainer. Help freelancers and small businesses manage finances.
- **[SEO Specialist / Content Strategist](#)** — $1.5K-5K per client. Optimize websites, build content strategies for agencies and SaaS.

> **Why start here:** You validate market demand immediately. Clients pay within 30 days if they're getting value. No guessing.

---

### Products & Tools (Digital + SaaS) — 12 options

**Revenue timeline:** 3-18 months | **Startup cost:** $0-5K

Both digital products and SaaS tools share one goal: create once, sell infinitely. Scale without being limited by your time.

**Start lightweight (digital products), graduate to SaaS if you want higher revenue.**

#### Digital Products — Low barrier to entry

- **[Online Course](#)** — $97-997 per course. Leverage existing expertise or audience.
- **[Templates & Checklists](#)** — $19-99 each. Sell systematized solutions on Gumroad. (Fastest to launch: 2-4 weeks)
- **[Newsletter/Membership](#)** — $10-100/month subscriptions. Build audience first, monetize later.
- **[Stock Media](#)** — Passive royalties. Upload photos/videos to Shutterstock, Getty, Adobe Stock.
- **[WordPress Themes & Plugins](#)** — $9-999 per theme. Evergreen products that sell forever.
- **[Ebook](#)** — $9-47 on Amazon KDP. Minimal upfront cost, long tail sales. (Easiest: write + upload)

#### SaaS & Tools — Higher revenue, longer timeline

- **[AI Tool](#)** — $19-99/month subscriptions. Build niche tools using OpenAI/Claude APIs. (3-6 months to MVP)
- **[Productivity Software](#)** — $9-99/month. Solve a specific problem (scheduling, invoicing, etc.).
- **[Browser Extension](#)** — Free + premium tier. Grammar tools, SEO checkers, password managers.
- **[API & Integration Service](#)** — $29-299/month. Help businesses connect platforms (Zapier, Make clones).
- **[Niche SaaS](#)** — $49-499/month. Build software for underserved industries. (Highest revenue, 12-18 months)
- **[Automation Tool](#)** — $19-199/month. Automate repetitive tasks, charge per run or user.

> **Choose digital products if:** You want to launch fast, have limited technical skills, or want to test market demand before investing heavily.
> **Choose SaaS if:** You're technical, want higher revenue per customer, and can commit 6-18 months to development.
> **Smart path:** Build digital products first to validate demand + build audience, then build SaaS for the same market.

